# Mermaid in docs: parse-safe style

When adding or editing Mermaid diagrams (especially `flowchart`), use a **parse-safe** style to avoid Mermaid parser errors across renderers (GitHub/Cursor/Markdown previews).

## Rules

- **Always quote node/subgraph labels**:
  - Prefer `Node["text"]` (or `Node("text")`) over `Node[text]` when the label contains punctuation, parentheses, slashes, or non-ASCII symbols.
  - Prefer `subgraph X["label"]` over `subgraph X[label]`.
- **Never use `\n` inside labels**. Use HTML breaks instead:
  - Use `<br/>` inside the quoted label text.
- **Avoid unescaped special characters in unquoted labels**. If you need them, **quote the label**.

## Examples

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  subgraph Apps["apps/"]
    UI["tooling-ui (Vite)"]
    BE["tooling-backend (API)"]
  end

  Idea["Идея в inbox"] --> Park["Остаётся в inbox<br/>(можно вернуться позже)"]
```

